---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Automated English Toxicity Detection"
  period="Mar to Jun 2024"
  tags={['NLP', 'BERT', 'LSTM', 'Scikit-learn', 'Python', 'Jupyter']}
  github="https://github.com/eralds/Automated-English-Toxicity-Detection"
  description="A benchmark of classical ML and deep learning approaches for detecting toxic content in English text."
>
  <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Toxicity detection is a core problem in content moderation: automatically identifying harmful, offensive, or
        abusive language at scale. This project benchmarked a wide range of ML approaches, from classical feature-based
        methods to transformer models, to understand the trade-offs between accuracy, complexity, and training cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Approaches Compared</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Classical ML (baselines)</p>
          <p class="text-sm">SVM and Random Forests combined with TF-IDF and Word2Vec embeddings. Fast to train and interpretable, but limited by the quality of bag-of-words representations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">LSTM (deep learning)</p>
          <p class="text-sm">GPU-optimized LSTM networks trained on token sequences. Captures word order and short-range context better than classical methods.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">BERT (best results)</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Fine-tuned BERT-based models achieved the highest classification accuracy by leveraging pre-trained bidirectional language understanding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Ensemble methods</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Combination strategies across model families to test if ensembling could close the gap between classical and deep approaches.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Tech Stack</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {[
          { label: 'Deep Learning', value: 'PyTorch, Hugging Face Transformers' },
          { label: 'Classical ML', value: 'Scikit-learn' },
          { label: 'Embeddings', value: 'TF-IDF, Word2Vec' },
          { label: 'Language', value: 'Python (Jupyter Notebooks)' },
        ].map(({ label, value }) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-1">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-800">{value}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ProjectLayout>
